title: Victims In Deadly Frayser Shooting Identified
content:

MEMPHIS, TN
MEMPHIS, TN (localmemphis.com)--Two victims have been identified following a shooting Monday night.
According to Memphis police, 13-year-old Letara Jones died after a neighbor's gun accidentally fired through the ceiling of a Corning Village apartment in Frayser. The shots hit the teenager and grazed a 12-week-old baby. Jones was taken to Le Bonheur Children's Hospital where she died.
20-year-old Daniel Lusk died from return gunfire. Police say Lusk was in the upstairs apartment when a suspect shot and killed him.
No arrests have been made.
